
[1]protector

   PROTECT'OR, n. One that defends or shields from injury, evil or
   oppression; a defender; a guardian. The king or sovereign is, or ought
   to be, the protector of the nation; the husband is the protector of his
   wife, and the father of his children.

   1. In England, one who formerly had the care of the kingdom during the
   king's minority; a regent. Cromwell assumed the title of lord
   Protector.

   2. In catholic countries, every nation and every religious order has a
   protector residing at Rome. He is a cardinal, and called cardinal
   protector.
